    "narrative": "The Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is led today by **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.25), both of whom benefit significantly from favorable matchups against pitchers with xERAs above 4.50. **Mickey Moniak** is our top play, capitalizing on a 14% park factor boost and a strong platoon advantage against Javier, while **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** leverages an elite 15% SP skill adjustment against Severino to anchor our offensive floor. **James Wood** also earns a Strong start (73.87) primarily due to the leadoff spot and his ability to exploit the high xERA of McGreevy. We are closely monitoring the lineups for **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Max Muncy**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, and **Jose Caballero**; any deviation from the projected batting order will impact their run-scoring potential, particularly for players like **Kyle Karros** and **Jose Caballero**, who are already penalized by lower-third lineup placement.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Trevor Story**, who posted a 46.37 score. While his base projection was solid, he was ultimately sidelined in favor of higher-efficiency options due to a negative wind flag and a challenging matchup against Drohan that stifled his ceiling. We are keeping a close eye on **Corbin Carroll** (63.31); despite a slight negative platoon adjustment against Peterson, his elite speed remains a vital component of our strategy given the scarcity of stolen bases in this league. With **Josh Naylor** confirmed out, our bench remains thin, but the current configuration maximizes our daily efficiency. We will continue to evaluate the utility of **Austin Riley** and **Alex Freeland**, though both were deemed lower-efficiency plays compared to our active roster for today\u2019s slate.",
